            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670336402484-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670336402484-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670336402484-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670336402484-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670336402484-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5 min or until softened and starting to caramelise</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670336406802-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670336406802-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670336406802-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670336406802-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1670336406802-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>to the pan with the <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> ground coriander</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil then cook for 3 min or until reduced to a curry-like consistency</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670336413043-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1670336413043-x400.jpg",
